{"title":"Orange Switch 6 Team makes Orange Factory Racing spec available to everyone","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/20/orange-switch-6-team-makes-orange-factory-racing-spec-available-to-everyone/","date":1632132015000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053811/orange-switch-6-team-factory-race-spec-formula-suspension-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"orange switch 6 team factory race spec tom wilson\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053811/orange-switch-6-team-factory-race-spec-formula-suspension-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053811/orange-switch-6-team-factory-race-spec-formula-suspension-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053811/orange-switch-6-team-factory-race-spec-formula-suspension-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053811/orange-switch-6-team-factory-race-spec-formula-suspension-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053811/orange-switch-6-team-factory-race-spec-formula-suspension.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-271912\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Orange Bikes have released an all-singing all-dancing build of their mixed-wheel enduro race bike; the Orange Switch 6 Team. This is the bike the Orange Factory Race Team have been slaying EWS tracks on all season. The super tuneable high-end Italian suspension from Formula is the standout highlight of the build. Here’s team rider, Tom Wilson, putting the Switch 6 Team through its paces on some Tweed Valley gold.</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/HPhsO8kg6f0?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><h2>Orange Switch 6 Team</h2><p>The Orange Factory Race Team bike is now available to Joe Public. As ridden by Joe Connell and Tom Wilson, the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/09/16/orange-drops-switch-6-mullet-stage-5-6-29er-trail-bikes-plus-3-emtbs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Orange Switch 6</a> Team gets a custom tuned <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/09/22/formula-mod-coil-shock-springs-to-life-reshim-able-by-you-with-three-cts-valves/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Formula MOD Coil Shock</a> damping 145mm of rear wheel travel. It’s pretty special, tuned to introduce progression and support into a linear spring rate on a single-pivot frame. The shock can be further tuned by you, the rider, by swapping out the CTS (Compression Tuning System) valves to suit your riding style.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20054453/orange-switch-6-race-formula-mod-coil-shock.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20054453/orange-switch-6-race-formula-mod-coil-shock.jpg\" alt=\"orange switch 6 race formula mod coil shock joe connell bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20054453/orange-switch-6-race-formula-mod-coil-shock.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20054453/orange-switch-6-race-formula-mod-coil-shock-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20054453/orange-switch-6-race-formula-mod-coil-shock-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20054453/orange-switch-6-race-formula-mod-coil-shock-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20054453/orange-switch-6-race-formula-mod-coil-shock-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>It’s a very simple procedure that doesn’t require use of special tools. You can effectively change the shim stack to tune the shock’s compression damping tune. For any other shock on the market, you’d be looking at spending several hundred dollars getting a custom tuning specialist to do this for you, plus a number of weeks off the bike.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053804/orange-factory-racing-switch-6-formula-selva-fork.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053804/orange-factory-racing-switch-6-formula-selva-fork.jpg\" alt=\"orange switch 6\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053804/orange-factory-racing-switch-6-formula-selva-fork.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053804/orange-factory-racing-switch-6-formula-selva-fork-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053804/orange-factory-racing-switch-6-formula-selva-fork-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053804/orange-factory-racing-switch-6-formula-selva-fork-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053804/orange-factory-racing-switch-6-formula-selva-fork-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20053804/orange-factory-racing-switch-6-formula-selva-fork-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The Orange Switch 6 Team also gets a Formula Selva S 29″ 160mm travel fork, also tuneable with two CTS valves to choose from, plus the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/06/25/video-how-formulas-neopos-dynamic-air-volume-spacers-work/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">NeoPos</a> compressible volume spacers that give the fork a more linear curve.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20055939/orange-switch-6-team-formula-cura-4-brakes.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20055939/orange-switch-6-team-formula-cura-4-brakes.jpg\" alt=\"formula cura 4\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20055939/orange-switch-6-team-formula-cura-4-brakes.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20055939/orange-switch-6-team-formula-cura-4-brakes-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20055939/orange-switch-6-team-formula-cura-4-brakes-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20055939/orange-switch-6-team-formula-cura-4-brakes-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/20055939/orange-switch-6-team-formula-cura-4-brakes-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Suspension is not the only Formula real estate on the bike; it also gets their 4-piston <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/05/10/new-formula-cura-4-mountain-bike-brakes-get-overpowered-oversized/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cura 4</a> brakes with 203mm rotors front and rear.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>The Orange Switch 6 Team retails at £5200 and is available at Orange dealers from today.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.orangebikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>OrangeBikes.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"66dc9bdcbeba91dcf5fc5beb2e41f45985ca0bb8a9cdeab22b2cfdfb3308f8b5","category":"Cycling"}